      "notes": "<p align=\"center\"> <img width=\"100%\" src=\"media://assets/markers.png\"/>\n\nMarkers help you label and navigate specific points in your project, making it easier to organize and reference key moments.\n\nThey are useful for transferring timing cues from a DAW or highlighting important events in your haptic clip.\n\n/newpage\n<p align=\"center\"><video width=\"100%\" src=\"media://assets/marker.mp4\" autoplay loop/></p>To create a marker, enable the Marker tool (shortcut M) and click on the point you want to annotate in the editor.\n\nIn the Marker tab on the right, you can add a name or description to the marker, or delete it using the bin icon.\n\nTo <b>reposition</b> a marker, simply drag its icon horizontally within the editor.",
