      "markers": [],
      "notes": "An emphasis point is a brief, crisp haptic feedback lasting only a few tenths of a second, creating a short, sharp sensation. \n\nEmphasis points appear as blue vertical bars on the amplitude envelope.\n\n<p align=\"center\"> <img width=\"100%\" src=\"media://assets/emphasis.png\"/>\n\nTo add emphasis points, use the Emphasis tool, accessible from the Tool Bar or by pressing the shortcut E.\n\n/newpage\nClick on the desired spot to add a point, then choose the sharpness level from the popup menu. \n\nClick the rounded icon on the left for a soft emphasis, click the icon on the right for a sharper emphasis.\n\nYou can fine-tune the sharpness level anytime using the Sharpness slider in the Design tab.\n\n<p align=\"center\"> <img width=\"100%\" src=\"media://assets/emphasisslider.png\"/>\n\nTo delete an emphasis point, press the bin icon or the Delete key. You can remove multiple points by selecting them and clicking the bin icon in the Design tab.\n\n",
