      "lastUpdate": 1750428831236,
      "notes": "Use the Trim tool to adjust the length of your clip.\n\nTo access the Trim tool, select the Trim icon from the Tool Bar, press the shortcut key T, or click the Trim button in the Design tab. Activating the Trim tool moves the editor view to the end of the clip and displays a trim bar.\n\n<p align=\"center\">\n<video width=\"100%\" src=\"media://assets/trim.mp4\" autoplay loop/>\n\n\n/newpage\n\n<b>Adjusting Clip Length</b>\nDrag the trim bar left or right to set the new clip duration. Alternatively, enter the desired length directly in the New Clip Duration field on the Design tab.\n\nConfirm your changes by pressing Enter, clicking the Confirm button, or clicking the checkmark icon above the trim line.\n\n<p align=\"center\"> <img width=\"100%\" src=\"media://assets/trimconfirm.png\"/>\n\nOnce set, the exported clip will end at the trim point, and any content beyond it will be excluded.\n\n/newpage\n<b>Editing the Trim Position</b>\nTo change an existing trim point, simply edit the value in the New Clip Duration field in the Design tab.\n\n<b>Reverting the Trim</b>\nTo undo trimming, click the Revert button in the Design tab or click the bin icon in the trim widget while editing the trim line.\n\n\n<p align=\"center\"> <img width=\"100%\" src=\"media://assets/revert.png\"/>\n"
    },
