      },
      "lastUpdate": 1750428164932,
      "notes": "Let’s start by connecting your headset to the Desktop App so you can audition your haptic effects.\n\nClick ‘Not connected’ in the top right corner of the Desktop App.\n\n**Install the App on Your Headset**\nClicking ‘Not connected’ will open a panel, select ‘Install App’ to be redirected to the Meta Quest Store webpage. From there, install the app on your device.\n\n<img width=\"100%\" src=\"media://./assets/connect.png\" />\n\n/newpage\n**Launch the App and Connect**\nOpen the app on your headset. You can connect either wirelessly or using a USB-C cable.\nFollow the on-screen prompts to connect your device. \n\nWhen prompted, select your computer from the list and enter the code displayed in the Desktop App.\n\n<img width=\"100%\" src=\"media://./assets/code.png\" />\n\n/newpage\n\n**Start Auditioning**\nOpen a project in the Desktop App, it will automatically sync to your connected device for real-time auditioning.\n\nWe recommend Meta Quest 3 & Touch Pro controllers as they offer the highest fidelity haptic feedback.\n\n<img width=\"100%\" src=\"media://./assets/controller.png\" />\n"
    },
    {
      "clipId": "8591d391-586d-469c-a77a-99bcde982d13",
